      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Promponents like Arthur Jensen and Richard Herrnstein have historically driven these arguments, often referencing early aggregate studies on IQ scores across diverse populations. They frequently point to Flynn effect regressions as proof that genetic influence, rather than just societal change, underlies intelligence shifts. Specific research often focuses on pair-wise comparisons, selecting data segments that support pre-existing hypotheses about innate group differences. These researchers insist on controlling for measured environmental variables while highlighting unexplained genetic variance.",
